<HEADLINE>
<P>
THIS FIGHT NEEDED MONEY-BACK GUARANTEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In answer to Earl Gustkey's story, "No Mas Still Baffles Experts": What 
experts? 
</P>
<P>
I ain't no expert but I don't think Duran just had it within himself to take 
the dive he was supposed to take. He obviously did the obvious "No Mas'' and 
walked away. 
</P>
<P>
FRANK CARLISI, Calabasas 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA120989-0034 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 145912 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 9, 1989, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 3; Column 2; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
83 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
THIS FIGHT NEEDED MONEY-BACK GUARANTEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No mas, no mas. 
</P>
<P>
Pay-per-view fights should come complete with a money-back guarantee. If the 
performance isn't appealing by the midway point, you can call in and ask for a 
refund. I'd rather watch a Rocky film. Or the WWF. 
</P>
<P>
Cease boxing's Senior Circuit before one of them actually has to throw a punch. 
The Hearns-Leonard draw was a joke and I've seen better fights in the Coliseum 
stands than the Duran-Leonard waltz I got suckered into paying for Thursday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
GARY MIEREANU, Northridge 
</P>
</TEXT>
