<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE A COACH TO BASH ONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am only 26 and was not around for the birth of the now famous and widely 
accepted "gutty little Bruins" notion, but I don't subscribe to it. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA was 5-4-1 against USC in the 1980s, and three of the four losses were by a 
total of nine points. The Bruins had an average margin of victory of 11.2 
points in their five wins over USC. 
</P>
<P>
I'm sorry to confuse USC fans with the facts, but UCLA had the upper hand in 
the 1980s. I wish the "gutty little Trojans" better luck in the 1990s. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL WEISS, Westwood 
</P>
