<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORONA BEATS CANYON SPRINGS IN DIVISION V 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CORONA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Keith Brockie recovered a bad center snap in the end zone in the second quarter 
to give Corona High School a 14-10 lead, and the Panthers rode that margin into 
their first Southern Section Division V football championship, beating Moreno 
Valley Canyon Springs Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon Springs (12-2) opened up a 10-point lead in the first quarter on a 
45-yard touchdown pass play from Kevin Gormont to Eric Zomalt and a 24-yard 
field goal by Richard Couch. 
</P>
<P>
Corona (10-4) countered with 14 second-quarter points on six-yard touchdown 
pass from Steve Bernier to Gabe Rincon and Keith Brockie's recovery. 
</P>
<P>
The second half was dominated by the defenses. 
</P>
<P>
Corona, the No. 3 team from the Mountain View League, lost earlier in the year 
to league runner-up Canyon Springs, 34-12. Corona defeated league champion 
Norco, 28-14, last week in the semifinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
