<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARPINTERIA WINS IN LAST MINUTE, 24-21 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA BARBARA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carpinteria's B.J. Shamblin caught a three-yard pass from Coley Candaele with 
17 seconds remaining to give Carpinteria a 24-21 win over Tehachapi Friday 
night at San Marcos High in the Southern Section Division IX title game. 
</P>
<P>
The victory gave Carpinteria its second title in three years. 
</P>
<P>
Carpinteria, which finished the season 13-1, jumped to a 10-0 lead when Jose 
Hernandez scored on a 17-yard run and Robert Villa added a 25-yard field goal. 
</P>
<P>
Tehachapi's tandem of quarterback Ryan Grimes and receiver La Vail Johnson then 
went to work and scored on touchdowns of 65, 22 and nine yards. The third score 
gave Techahapi (12-2) a 21-17 fourth-quarter lead. 
</P>
<P>
Candaele finished the game with 13 completions in 25 attempts for 137 yards. 
Izak Ondre was Carpinteria's leading rusher with 108 yards in 15 carries. 
</P>
