<HEADLINE>
<P>
MURPHY MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Peter Rainer criticizes Eddie Murphy for giving up those great moments on 
"Saturday Night Live" for commercial films that -- according to Rainer -- don't 
measure up to Murphy's talents ("Murphy &amp; Pryor's Star Trek," Nov. 24). How 
come Rainer doesn't criticize other "Saturday Night" graduates such as Chevy 
Chase, who continues to make those innocuous "on the road" movies; or Bill 
Murray, who did "Ghostbusters II," a film that didn't make me laugh once; or 
Dan Aykroyd, who is to the art of acting what apartheid is to compassion. 
</P>
<P>
Of course it has nothing to do with the fact that all these are white and Eddie 
Murphy is black. Of course not! 
</P>
<P>
RICK EDELSTEIN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
