<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: LONG BEACH PLAN FOR AUTO MALL SUFFERS 
SETBACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Long Beach's attempts to keep its auto dealers from fleeing to other cities hit 
a major setback this week when neighboring Signal Hill signed exclusive 
negotiating agreements with four Long Beach dealers who have decided they would 
rather do business in Signal Hill. 
</P>
<P>
Both cities are planning auto malls. But while Long Beach has yet to sign up a 
dealer, Signal Hill already has signed up two Long Beach dealerships and will 
begin finalizing agreements with the four. Signal Hill was able to offer the 
dealers a better financial arrangement and an earlier construction date than 
Long Beach, which started planning its mall after Signal Hill. 
</P>
<P>
Susan Shick, Long Beach community development director, said the city will 
continue to pursue other dealers and perhaps rethink the mall proposal to 
include retail space. 
</P>
