<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NFL CLEARS RYAN OF BOUNTY ON COWBOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An NFL investigation has cleared Philadelphia Coach Buddy Ryan of offering 
bounties to his players for injuring Dallas Cowboy players. Dallas Coach Jimmy 
Johnson accused Ryan of that after a game on Thanksgiving Day. 
</P>
<P>
The league warned, however, that severe penalties would be exacted against any 
team engaging in such activities. 
</P>
<P>
The NFL said its findings were based on an investigation by Commissioner Paul 
Tagliabue. 
</P>
<P>
Ryan said the statement confirmed what he has been saying all along: "The 
Philadelphia Eagles did not place any bounties on Dallas players." 
</P>
<P>
Cowboy kicker Luis Zendejas was disappointed by the ruling. 
</P>
<P>
"All I know is that I told the truth," Zendejas said. "I guess it all depends 
on how lightly the guys who were investigating it took it. I guess they didn't 
take it too seriously." 
</P>
<P>
The teams will play again Sunday at Philadelphia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
