</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reggie Rogers, a former Detroit Lion defensive end, was convicted of negligent 
homicide in the deaths of three teen-agers in a drunk driving accident. 
</P>
<P>
Rogers faces a maximum two-year prison sentence on each misdemeanor charge of 
negligent homicide. Sentencing is scheduled Jan. 16. 
</P>
<P>
Rogers, a No. 1 draft pick of the Lions from the University of Washington in 
1987, suffered a broken neck, a partially amputated thumb and other injuries in 
the accident last year. He was released by the Lions in training camp last 
summer. 
</P>
