<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GARY COLEMAN'S MOTHER SUES FOR A 
CONSERVATOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Gary Coleman's mother has filed suit to have a conservator named for the 
21-year-old former child star, claiming that a man hired as a chauffeur is 
managing his affairs and that Coleman is "at risk of financial exploitation." 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles Superior Court suit filed by Edmonia Sue Coleman charges that 
the nearly $7-million estate of the former star of NBC's "Diff'rent Strokes" is 
now being controlled by a friend of Coleman's named Dion Mial. 
</P>
<P>
Mial was hired by Coleman as his driver and "go-fer" at a salary of $325 a week 
and is now overseeing the estate, court papers said. 
</P>
<P>
Coleman has fired his business manager, agent, entertainment attorney and his 
parents in their role as personal managers and trustees. 
</P>
<P>
The petition, filed earlier this week, charges that Mial has cut off contact 
between the actor and his parents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
