<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTRACT POST OFFICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Dallas M. Jackson and Janice L. Jones / Los Angeles 
Times, Graphics by Doris Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In this season of heavy mailing, you are probably dreading a trip to the post 
office, where the lines are sure to be longer than those for fresh vegetables 
in Moscow. An alternative might be to try one of the more than 50 small, 
contract postal stations scattered throughout the county. (Unless noted, these 
stations are closed on Sundays.) 
